text: Freshly made chee cheong fun (steamed rice flour sheet) has a slightly chewy texture. The thin sheets are complemented by a sauce that is flavorful without being overpowering. The chili paste adds some kicks to the overall taste but oily.
Freshly made chee cheong fun had good texture. But chilli and meat filling very mediocre.

Cheong Fun is made on the spot by friendly sis. I think the texture to ingredients ratio is fantastic.

Uniquely comes with cabbage & bean sprouts at the bottom of cheong fun (take note to request it out if not as adventurous)

Will definitely stop by in the vicinity again
Very unique cheong chong fun, not same than other style. Not bad, and big portions
This stall sell char Kuey Teow in the afternoon. Not the best but for neighbourhood standard, is considered quite good Hor.
